members.member:
Opens a connection with QuickBooks. This call is always made to
start an SDK interaction with QuickBooks. It must precede the rest
of the session and it is terminated by a call to closeConnection.

@param appID    a unique identifier for the calling applicaton, may be null
@param appName  the name for the calling applicaton

Process one or more qbXML requests. The requests are contained in
a string and must adhere to the qbXML specification. When processing of
the requests is complete, this call returns with a string that contains
the XML responses.

@param ticket   a ticket acquired in the beginSession call
@param xmlInput contains the qbXML requests from the caller

@return         a string containing the qbXML response to the requests

Returns the name of the current file that is open in QuickBooks. May be used
to confirm that the right company file is open before issuing any requests
that will change the file.

@param ticket   a ticket acquired in the beginSession call

@return         a string containing the name of the open company file

